Some interesting notes:

They're waiting to see if OUTCOMES are better - productivity seems to be
higher.
Real problem is onboarding and maintaining culture
Fatigue is increasing; is/how is remote work sustainable?
All the research into innovation shows a sense of belonging is necessary.

They surveyed ~2k senior level execs and most felt that remote workers
would comprise 25-75% of their entire workforce by 2021. (I'll get the
exact numbers and breakdown when they send it out.) Overall, if we can
target this transition I'd say we'd have a very healthy target customer
base!

